DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "answerHints.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);

##############################################

Context("LimitedNumeric");

$b=random(2,5,1);
$c=random(2,5,1);
$d=random(2,5,1);
$a=random($b*$c*$d+1,$b*$c*$d+10,1);

$ans=Compute($a-$b*($c)*$d);

##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Evaluate this expression:

    [`` [$a]-[$b]([$c])[$d] =  ``]  [________]{$ans}


END_PGML

##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

Since there is no operation symbol between [`[$b]`] and [`([$c])`], and between [`([$c])`] and [`[$d]`], it implies multiplication.

       [``
            \begin{aligned}[t]
           [$a]-[$b]([$c])[$d] 
              &= [$a]-[$b*$c] \cdot [$d] \\
              &= [$a]-[$b*$c*$d] \\
              & = [$ans] 
              \end{aligned}
        ``]

In the second step, we wrote in a multiplication symbol (a dot) between [`[$b*$c]`] and [`[$d]`]. This was needed to avoid confusion.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();


